content.detailedDescription:
I generally do not post on fb but this was just to bizzar last night.
 at approximately 8:30 pm on 8/29/2015 we witnessed 2 then a 3rd strange glowing lights ? in the southern hemisphere moving east very quick then stopping for about 3 -5 seconds. then one by one they shot straight up into the atmosphere it took 3 -4 seconds to disappear. no sounds no red or green blinking lights . at first they appeared to be chinese lanterns with same glowing color. for sure they were not. and they were not helicopters taking off nor landing @ cleveland clinic ( twinsburg ) way to large and far up to be someone playing with 3 drones . 3 of us watched in amazement. im not a ufo chaser or anything of the sort , i am open minded to ?? . i decided to report this 12 hrs later to local authorities. this was just way to bizzar not to say anything. woundering if anyone else happen to see the same thing last night

content.detailedDescription:
My husband and i were coming home to my parents house, where we temporarily lived, and it was later at night between 11:00 p.M. to 12:00 a.M. we had been over visiting my in-laws and were returning home. we could see as we were pulling up to the house and parking in the driveway a bright light in the west.  the light seemed unusually bright to us.  as we parked the car in the driveway, we noticed this light/air "craft" was close to us and we crouched down beside the car because we were scared because we didn't know what it was.  the light was coming out in front of the ufo, almost like a headlight, which made us originally feel it was maybe a helicopter coming or airplane, but it was very low in the sky which is what made us confused about its identity at first.  

as we crouched by the car, the ufo passed over top of us.  it was in a diamond/chevron shape, but the strange thing about it was it made absolutely no noise whatsoever.  we thought how strange it was that such a huge thing could make no noise at all and make no noise traveling at the speed that it did as it covered a lot of ground.  we saw it in the distance and in the time it took us to pull into the driveway and park, it was basically almost on top of us.  it traveled in a straight line never wavering.  

anyway, it passed over us and continued on its way east.  we watched it until it was no longer in sight.  it was a moonlit night, so i remember distinctly seeing the outline of the craft as well as it being blacker than anything i have seen before.  i believe i could see huge window "shapes" on the side that we saw.  we went into the house and explained what we saw to my parents, but never saw anything like it ever again.  i was actually afraid to go to sleep that night and the next few nights because i was afraid whatever was in that thing must have seen us. 

my mother had told me that a few years later, she had witnessed a ufo.  it was during the daytime and much, much higher in the sky than what we had seen.
content.summary: Saw a bright light out west moving east.  we got out of car and crouched down.  the ufo flew over us very quietly and continued on its way east.

content.detailedDescription: Since moving into my 11th floor apartment, i have been taking pictures of the sunset over the past 10 months. one night, i was looking through the pictures and noticed there was this object in many of the pictures. none of the daytime photos showed any objects, only those taken during the sunset. they were not visible to the naked eye. i realized that some of the pictures had a green circle, and others had an aura around it. the green circles are clearly seen in pictures on both cloudy and clear days. i have taken over 50 pictures with the object, but never noticed until a few weeks ago. the object is very tiny and thought it was just the reflection of the sunlight in the camera. the object can be seen in locations around lake erie and sunsets in the pictures. i can see the object moving around from one picture to the next. the object is consistent with color and shape, as well as the aura around the green circle.The aura is a dome shape, creamy color. it is prominent on the right and left sides, and is consistent in all pictures. only one picture captured the object as red, which was out of focus. i did not ever see this object with my own eyes, but have captured many pictures. i thought i was seeing things, and it was a reflection of light somehow.
content.summary: Taking pictures of the sunset, i have captured over 50 pictures of a green circle, some with an aura around it. they appear to be over lake erie.

content.detailedDescription:
I was preparing dinner on the deck, south side of the house. clear night and almost full moon. 
it was dark so approx. 9pm.
i thought i would take photo of the candles on the patio table i was preparing. then the moon appeared from behind the tall evergreen trees.
the brightness of it made me think what a lovely photo so i took three, photos. 
i did not notice the orb until i loaded the photos onto the computer.
so i never saw it from the deck with my eye. just the camera saw this.
i went about preparing the meal and one thing was strange, the candles didn't flicker when on the patio table, like no breeze whatsoever very still.
i put the photos on face book and asked my face book friends what it might be??? and the response was mars.
in one of the photos you will notice the orb on the right. not as bright.
other two photos where taken seconds later.
content.summary: Full moon/the orb was on the moons left side, captured by the camera not my eye

content.detailedDescription: I was at home in the backyard looking at the sky, when i noticed extremely bright green and blue pulsating lights in the distance traveling west.  the lights were so much brighter than anything, and was moving at a very fast speed, when it suddenly accelerated at a 45 degree angle down to the right then leveled out traveling east, then shot straight up at extreme speeds then down behind the mountain.  it was mesmerizing to behold, i ran inside and grabbed my friend to come see it.  we stood outside and it wasn't there, so we waited there for a minute looking at the mountain it had dropped down behind.  it then came shooting up at mind boggling speed then darted left, right, shot down then up again and behind the mountain once more.  we waited another minute or two, and it never came back.  it was a life impacting experience.  i have no doubt what we saw was nothing of this earth.  i was a us marine i know what aircraft looks like and what they can do, and that was nothing we have.
content.flightPath: Straight-line path,Path with directional change,Path then hovering
content.summary: Blue and green pulsating light covered object flying wildly in the sky

content.detailedDescription: It was a saturday night at around 720 or 730. the eagles pre-season game was on against the ravens. me and my friend ordered cheese steaks at a pizzeria that is less than two blocks away. i stayed and watched the game as she went to get the food. as she was walking down orianna street (right off girard ave)going to cambridge street where she lives, she looked up in the sky and saw three white rectangles. there was a moon in the daytime sky, although the sun was very close to setting, and to the left of the moon were these three white rectangles. she was walking carrying the food and looking at them, she stopped briefly and moved to the side to see if maybe somehow they were being created by a reflection (she didn't think they were, but had no idea what she was seeing). after realizing that they were indeed in the sky she rushed down the rest of the block and got me. she came in and said "come outside! i want you to see something in the street!" i got right up (this was unlike her, she wasn't screaming but she was slightly urgent) and she told me to put on my shoes but i told her its ok...So i went out without my shoes which really isn't a good idea in the city. i thought we were gonna look at something in the street, not in the sky. she took me halfway down the block and was soooo disappointed "theyre gone!" she said. i asked her what and she described seeing three white rectangles in the sky off to the left of the moon and said that they were just there. they weren't moving or anything. so i got as much information as i could from her and recreated a photo to show everyone what she saw. the recreation is fairly accurate. she's not really interested that much in ufos and has never seen one before. to her this is something that will never be known (what she saw). these were not aircraft carrying banners, we see them all the time and know exactly what they look like. she observed these for about 10 to 15 seconds. it was a very clear sky. she had her contact lenses in. the time it took for me to go outside and look in the sky was less than 30 seconds. she has no idea how big they were or how far they were, but she said they definetly didn't look like something you could start walking towards and soon find yourself standing under...Which leads me to believe they were kind of far away. they were motionless and noiseless. she said they looked exactly the same color of the moon in the daylight, which was next to them. she said they appeared slightly luminous. the sun was setting behind them by the way. the photos are recreations that show kind of what she saw...One is the entire block and the other is me trying to recreate three rectangles and the moon. i don't have any photo editing programs so i cant recreate it exactly, but the rectangles were solid with clear definitions and were luminous like the moon in daylight.
content.summary: Three white rectangles observed hovering over philadelphia

thank you
manuel salvador

content.detailedDescription:
i love my sunsets on lake huron and i am known to take many pictures, however, i have never seen anything like this before. my family and i own a cottage on the ontario side of lake huron, 100 kms south of tobermory on the bruce peninsula.I was taking pictures of the sunset over lake huron facing west (of course) 

once home, i reviewed my photos and i enlarged picture 1-1-1 and i spotted the anomaly on the photograph. my daughter suggested that i check the other photos for the same anomaly to ensure that it wasnâ€™t dirt on my camera and the other 2 pictures are the result of that crop and zoom. i was astounded when i saw all of the objects. my sister and i recall the exact moment that i was taking the photographs and at no time did we see anything in the sky or hear anything at all. i do have other photos and i have all the originals if necessary. definitely ufos over the lake.
content.summary: Taking pictures of sunset over lake huron on ontario side and captured on camera

content.detailedDescription: I was fertilizing hay fields with my son and it started getting dark so i parked the tractor got off and looked into the night sky. i said to my son did that light move. he said yes. we both stood there and looked in amazement. it first moved left just a little, then back to the right and stopped. then it moved quickly away from us in an easterly direction, gaining altitude like it left the atmosphere. the entire event lasted less than 1 min. i looked at my son and said i think we just saw a ufo. i am a pilot; i own 2 small aircraft, and i have never seen anything like this in my life. the object was never close, my guess is it was 5-10 miles away. it looked at first like a huge star, but it was way too large compared to other stars in the sky. i know it was not a meteor, because the trajectory gained altitude as it exited the area and there was no trail behind it. i am not sure of the size, but it was about the size of a nickel held at arm's length as we were looking at it in the sky. when it left the area, it went due east and was out of sight in about 6 seconds gaining altitude.
content.summary: Very bright star like light moved right then left then appeared to exit atmosphere in 4-6 seconds

content.detailedDescription: I was doing laundry around 10:30pm on 8/28/2015, when i heard very loud helicopters close to the house. i stepped out in time to see two orange orbs followed closely by two helicopters flying over my house.The orbs had a bright orange red glow and were very small, like the size of a golf ball. they were flying in sync with each other and they were wobbling while flying in unison. the helicopters were right behind each one and they quickly flew out of sight.
content.summary: Two orange orbs being chased or followed by two military helicopters

content.detailedDescription: My wife & i left her mother's house at around 10:00pm tonight. as we were driving down the rural gravel road, my wife saw what she thought was a "star" or a "planet" in the sky. she immediately asked me & told me to look. i dod not see it. it had appeared & disappeared before i could see it. i immediately explained to her that it's cloudy & that it's not possible to see stars out tonight. then, i saw a light in the distance (further east) & asked if it was what she saw. she said "yes" but that it was not that far away. i thought what i was looking at was a cell phone or radio tower, but it became evident that it wasn't because it was moving across the sky from the east to the northwest. the light was red/orange & did not pulse or anything. i kept looking for navigation lights, but did not see any. the entire object was lit. it eventually ascended slowly into the clouds & disappeared. we started driving again & saw several people outside their home looking at the sky. we stopped & spoke to them to see if we could get a better understanding of what the lights may have been. they told us that they had watched them for 20 minutes. again, the lights made no noises whatsoever. i spent almost 10 years in the military, including 5 years in the united states air force. i know exactly what an aircraft looks like in the sky. i cannot explain what i saw tonight. i have tried to explain this as a chinese lantern, drone, or an aircraft of some sort. i simply can't. not with it changing directions, ascending & decending, etc. the part that really threw me off is the fact that the objects were completely quiet. despite them being below the clouds & fairly close to our position on the ground.
content.summary: Two orange/red lights, hovering & moving, no noise.

content.detailedDescription: My daughter and i were driving down a rural county road in sequim, wa around 9:40pm in late july 2015.  no street lights in vicinity.  to the left (west) we saw a flying object. what caught my attention was that it had red/orange pulsing glow to it and was flying in our direction. it then stopped and moved in the total opposite direction very quickly.  i have never witnessed a ufo, but this was so unusual that we pulled over and turned off the car to watch/listen.  it moved very fast and in several different directions. the movement and color were very unusual.  it was definitely not an airplane or a helicopter. they wouldn't be able to move in different directions that quickly.  also, the color was odd.  not like the blinking lights on an airplane or helicopter.  it was more of a pulsing red/orange glow...If that's how to describe it?  the experience was very unsettling as i have never witnessed anything like this in my life. we talk of it often as it really made us aware that ufo's can very well be real after witnessing this first hand.
content.summary: Ufo with red-orange lights in sequim area

content.detailedDescription: On 08282015 around 2330hrs i did observe a white round sphere shaped unexplained light in the eastern sky which shortly followed a plane that just flew over, this light moved very fast in several directions and went from east to then north and disappeared, a plane or searchlight could not move like this, the next evening around 2000 thru 2030hrs me and others did observe white ash substance falling from sky that almost looked like very light snowflakes falling on an 86 degree evening, when the substance was touched it would turn to powder like burnt ash does, i contacted the national weather service, the local sheriff's dept, and local fire dept ref to the white ash substance and there was no report of fire or burning in area anywhere and no one could offer explanation, there was no smoke smell or smoke seen prior to dark either, i did take pics of the ash substance but it was after dark and they did not turn out well, but i did save them anyway, the ash slightly covered our porch and vehicles, i have never seen anything like this before and was a police officer for nearly 10 years
content.summary: On 08282015 and 08292015 a white round dot light was seen in eastern sky shortly following an airplane moved eradically fast in several different directions, next day we had awhile ash substance fall from sky not sure if it's related to lights or not

content.detailedDescription: This happened august 29th at 9:55 p.M. when i was walking my dog up our street going west when i looked up the street noticing a bluish white light, at first i thought it was a planes nav lights because after a few seconds the light had changed to red, but the light was not blinking or moving it stayed red and seemed to be getting brighter and more vibrant at this time the object faded back to the bluish white light and began to move side to side for about 5 to 10 seconds not too much just enough to notice it wasn't stationary then it stopped and seemed to be hovering it had only been about 1 minute that i had been watching the object and at this time it change from the bluish white to red  and began to move up then down a few times it moved much more than the side to side motion and it didn't move fast it moved slow and steady. at this time i had reached the driveway to my house. before i went to get the camera i seen it changed into a yellowish orange cigar-shaped light or orb. before it change shape the bluish white light was a sphear or circle and the light seem to then turn a yellowish orange and stretch into the cigar shape. it was trippy!! at this point i ran to the camera by the time i made it back to the road the yellowish orange cigar shaped had turn back to the whitish blue orb and was still changing colors back from bluish white to red, the light did not seem to be blinking it seemed  as if the entire object was  fading in and out  from bluish white to red taking about 3 to 5 seconds to change from bluish white to red each time it changed. at this point it had been about two two and a half minutes total that i had watched the object. with camera in hand i started walking down the street to get closer to the object. as i was walking closer towards the object  it seem to be  either descending below the tree line or moving away  holding a steady red glow no longer changing from whitish blue to red. at this point i started to back away from the object to try and keep it in my view  but as i kept backing up keeping it my view it kept moving away (west) or getting lower. i had watched the object for probably about 4 to 5 minutes total. unfortunately well i was trying to take pictures or film,nothing would show up due to the streetlights interference on the camera  i did manage to take a video  but like i said with the street lights you could not see the orb  or any sign of it in the video. i don't know exactly how far away it was but the object most likely was a mile or so away and anywhere from 100 - 800 foot up i really couldn't say. i do know that it was very cloudy because it was about to rain and the light or orb was well below the cloud line. from the time i realized it was not an airplane a feeling of anxiousness excitement and curiosity had overwhelmed me and all i could keep thinking was please come closer so i could get a better view and a wonder of what it could be or who?!
content.flightPath: Stationary,Hovering then path,Path with directional change
content.summary: I was taking my dog for a walk when i looked up the street seen a bright white light that turned whitish blue then to a deep red as i went to get the camera it turn into a yellowish orange cigar-shaped when i got back it had returned  tobluish white orb s

content.detailedDescription: Driving east  bound on the highway on august 22, 2015 approx 9:30 p.M. an orange orb appeared in front of us overhead, traveling approx the speed of a helicopter and with no sound. it seemed to have no structure. we turned into a parking lot at which time we observed 2 more orbs traveling north to south at a gradual incline  at what seemed to be the same speed  as the first orb . all 3 orbs seemed to ascend to same height and follow the same path. as the 3 orbs reached a point when our view was obstructed by trees and houses, we noticed 2 more orbs. the height of the first 3 they maintained the same path . when this was over we left and about 2 hours later saw a 6th orb pass over and like the others this also made no sound . as a side note, a friend of mine who was a few miles south of where we were watching this happen,  saw the first 3 pass over, then hover for a brief time then start to head back north, then change direction again and head south and then just vanish . we also have several video clips of the orbs and we are sending pics, too. also we checked a ufo database and this is the 3rd sighting in the past month of objects like this .
content.summary: Orange orbs appeared in n. sky then ascended and traveled s. in a straight horizontal line

content.detailedDescription: While walking my dog i noticed two star like objects relatively close to each other (closed than normal for planes) proceeding west. another was going to the same point in the sky from a south east direction. another group of three approached from the north east going the same way as the others. all 6 entered the same cloud at various locations and did not reappear. may have all been jets/military but unknown for sure. strange event regardless.
content.summary: 6 lights converging at various speeds. faint single jet sound. 3 separate directions. groups of one,  two,  and three

content.detailedDescription: One evening just before dark between 8:30pm & 9:00pm on june 22,2012 i went out back for a smoke.  i had just lit my cigarette & took a few puffs & call it intuition or whatever but, i suddenly had the feeling to look over my left shoulder up over the tree line behind me.  i looked up & saw a "dime" sized round shaped object floating through the air. i kept listening for an engine noise of somekind but so quiet you could literally hear a pin drop! no birds or bugs churping, nothing! i couldn't make out how far the object was in the sky. my first thought was, i'll run inside & get my camera & take some pictures! then my second thought was, i'd better stay here & watch to see if it takes off suddenly!  you don't know how bad i struggled with this knowing no one would believe me unless i had some sort of proof! but at the time, it was more important for me to watch every moment of the object i was witnessing since it only happens maybe 1nce in a lifetime so i stayed! the whole event lasted about half way through my cigarette. i guess about 4 mins. in total. i couldn't believe what i was seeing! the hair literally raised up on the back of my neck & that's only happened 1 other time in my life! it literally made a straight-line pass over my house & passed over my aunt & uncles house through the treelines & slowly disappeared out of site! the surface of it looked "mirror-like" as if it were reflecting the faint clouds & blue sky around it. dark in color. no lights, no sound, no kind of emmissions whatsoever!  it never changed shape 1 bit on it's surface. you would think it would change shape as it went over the mountaintop. just looked like a dime sized ball shaped object. kind of pewter black in color. it was incredible! i went from feeling like i had just won the lottery to, oh wow, nobody is going to take me seriously if i tell them about this. so, it was a mixed bag of an encounter. i told a few of my relatives & after a few looks of,"this guy is smoking something" i just stopped talking. really a bummer to experience something so spectacular & then get ridiculed & labeled as being some sort of whacko for even mentioning ufo's. since then & even before then i have looked up in the sky at dark only & have seen lights going from one part of the sky to the other in less than a second fast like someone shining a very bright light in the sky only no beams being emitted from the ground to very slow glowing objects going in straight lines like a plane does only it looks like a star in the sky moving very slowly. i never really took the whole ufo thing seriously, even after seeing the lights zipping around like stars from one end to the other. my dad said they were satalites. i told him, i don't think satalites move that fast. since my siting i always make sure i look up like i always do to watch the stars. after watching a show about ufo's i searched sightings of ufo's on june 22, 2012 & all of these links with the same exact date popped up from surrounding states around me! that's when i decided to file this report. just in case you guys have heard of any sightings on this particular date around my area or surrounding states.  thanks for reading. sincerely, ford smith
content.summary: Looked over my left shoulder & there it was.

content.detailedDescription: Four objects following each other red/ orange no noise as they approached each one after the other appeared to dim. we thought they were moving straight up and away from us whereas each one slowly dimmed out until they were gone.
content.summary: Four red/orange objects following each other then each one dimmed out or flew straight up out of  sight

content.detailedDescription: I was on a road heading towards a football scrimmage that i filmed. i was in the passenger seat of the car. i saw it out of the corner of my eye as do to its weird shape. it looked like a small cigar shape "drone". it made a curved path in one direction, then changed into the opposite direction. then it disappeared after it went behind a pocket of trees. it turned with a very slow and smooth grace to it. during the actions of the object, i was confused a bit of what i was seeing. i know there are a lot of local birds in the area, however it never changed shape. afterwards i was generally weird out by the object, and how it just "appeared" out of nowhere.
content.summary: Very small looking. thought it might be bird, bu it stayed the same shape.

content.detailedDescription:
I was sitting on my back deck with my dog when i observed an orange glowing sphere traveling towards me from the north northwest. it was brighter than the stars and about the size of a golf ball at its closest from me and the. it took a slow turn towards the south and i watched it traveling away from me until it got too far to see anymore. 
it was orange in color, bright but not to the point it was shiny and is exactly like many of the videos of the strange orange lights in the sky posted on you tube. unfortunately my phone was in the house when i observed this object and the event lasted between 3 to 5 minutes. 
have there been any other reports of this object in upstate new york or any neighboring states last night?
content.summary: Orange light traveling about fighter jet speed coming from n-nw towards e-se then turned more south until it was out of sight

content.detailedDescription: Early morning orange orb/ufo over redhill park in upland/rancho cucamonga at 0512 this morning. it was surrounded with an orange flame, it was awesome. this was no plane or drone. it's propulsion system was silent, it paused and moved effortlessly to the southwest...
content.summary: Early morning orange orb/ufo over redhill park in upland/rancho cucamonga at 0512 this morning. it was surrounded with an orange flame, it was awesome. this was no plane or drone. it's propulsion system was silent, it paused and moved effortlessly
